  "text": "## Joint Accounts  \n**Q: Can I open a joint SmartSaver Account?**\nA: Yes. Two customers can hold one joint account.  \n**Q: Who can access the money in a joint account?**\nA: Either account holder can withdraw the full balance anytime. Both have equal rights.  \n**Q: What happens to a joint account if one person dies?**\nA: Surviving account holder retains the account. Estate of deceased person entitled to their share (typically 50%). Bank requires death certificate and legal documentation.  \n**Q: What if joint account holders split up?**\nA: Both retain legal rights to the full account balance. Either can freeze/close the account. We recommend legal advice (civil matter, not bank's decision).  \n---",
